  <title translate="true">Item Builder: Items, Images and Addendums</title>
  <body>
    <header>
      <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-align:right;"><image src="thinkgate.jpg" align="right" scale="43.00%" width="192" height="43" styleclass="Image Caption"></image></para>
      <para styleclass="Heading1"><text styleclass="Heading1" style="color:#ffffff;" translate="true">Item Builder: Items, Images and Addendums</text></para>
    </header>
    <para styleclass="Heading1"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="New_Add_icon4.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Heading1" style="font-size:12pt; color:#000000;"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="true" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="New_Add_icon4.bmp" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Heading1" style="font-size:12pt; color:#000000;"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can I upload test questions from Microsoft Word?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:48px; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; color:#000080;" translate="true">Currently there is not a way to upload questions from an external source. &#160;Questions must be manually entered into the item bank using the Add Item feature.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="New_Add_icon4.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Heading1" style="font-size:12pt; color:#000000;"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="New_Add_icon4.bmp" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Heading1" style="font-size:12pt; color:#000000;"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Are there any restrictions on image sizes?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:47px; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; color:#000080;" translate="true">The suggested size for images uploaded to the system is 300x300 dots per inch (dpi) for two column tests. &#160;Images on one column tests can be as large as 600x600 dpi.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1"></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><image src="New_Add_icon4.bmp" scale="100.00%" styleclass="Heading1" style="font-size:12pt; color:#000000;"></image><tab /><toggle type="dropdown" print-expanded="true" help-expanded="false" defaultstyle="false" src-collapsed="New_Add_icon4.bmp" src-expanded="hmtoggle_plus1.gif" styleclass="Heading1" style="font-size:12pt; color:#000000;"><caption translate="true"><![CDATA[Can I add questions to Elements that come directly from a text book?]]></caption></toggle></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"><table styleclass="Default" rowcount="1" colcount="1">
      <tr style="vertical-align:top">
        <td>
          <para styleclass="Normal" style="text-indent:0px; margin-right:0px; margin-left:48px; tabstops:none;"><text styleclass="Normal" style="font-family:Calibri; font-size:12pt; color:#000080;" translate="true">If a question is added from an external source such as a text book the copyright information must be filled in. &#160;The copyright drop down on the Item Profile screen will need to be changed to &apos;Yes&apos; and the credit field filled in with the proper information for the original source of the question.</text></para>
        </td>
      </tr>
    </table></para>
    <para styleclass="Heading1" style="text-indent:-18px; margin-left:18px;"></para>
